#Text=Rochester ( Indiana )
#Text=Rochester is the county seat of Fulton County , Indiana , USA , and is the only city there ( although there are a number of small towns ) .
#Text=Its name comes from the much larger city in New York , USA .
#Text=Its proximity to South Bend and Fort Wayne makes it a handy place to stay and maybe visit if everything closer is taken , without being too far away or too expensive .
#Text=Get in
#Text=Rochester 's located where Indiana 25 , Old US 31 , and Indiana 14 join up , and New US 31 loops around the south and west edges of the city .
#Text=The Fulton County Airport , for small private aircraft , is also a way to get in and out .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Driving yourself is the best way to get around .
#Text=Downtown is small enough to park at one spot and walk around , but this is n't feasible for the entire city .
#Text=Fulton County Transpo , ☏ +1574 223-4213 , ✉ fccoa@rtcol.com . 6:30AM-5PM Monday - Friday .
#Text=Fulton County 's only public transportation .
#Text=$1/stop in town , $3/stop elsewhere in the county , private fees for out-of-county needs , free will donation for ages 60+ .
#Text=See
#Text=Fulton County Museum , 37 E 375 N ( Follow US 31 north of Rochester for 4 miles .
#Text=Turn left on 375 N , then left again onto the driveway . ) , ☏ +1574 223-4436 . 9 AM-5 PM Monday - Saturday ( closed on holidays ) .
#Text=A collection of historical items from Fulton County and the surrounding area , as well as books and local experts to aid in research and other needed purposes .
#Text=There are sections about , among other things , old important buildings , early settlers , and the county 's claim to fame as being the Round Barn Capital of the World .
#Text=Four historical events are hosted by the museum and Fulton County Historical Society each year :
#Text=The Living History Faire in March , the Redbud Trail Rendezvous in April , the Historical Power Show in June , and the Trail of Courage in September .
#Text=Free will donation .
#Text=Lake Manitou .
#Text=The largest lake in Fulton County , Lake Manitou is located in the southeast part of the city and prized for its good fishing waters , natural beauty , and abundance of boat-friendly waters .
#Text=The spillway dam on the north side of the lake is also and interesting place to visit .
#Text=Tippecanoe River .
#Text=" The River of Lakes " goes through the northern part of Fulton County .
#Text=It 's fairly shallow and perfect for paddling .
#Text=Fulton County Courthouse .
#Text=Events
#Text=4th of July Fireworks , 545 N State Road 25 .
#Text=The night of the 4th of July sees a big fireworks show at the county airport ( do n't worry , there 's no planes coming or going at the time ! ) .
#Text=Chili Cook-off and Red Hot Car Show , 815 N Main Street .
#Text=Shiny cars and chili-loving people cover the courthouse lawn on the second Saturday of October .
#Text=Come out and enjoy samples of chili made on-the-spot by various local groups and see all kinds of rare cars !
#Text=Fulton County 4-H Fair , 1009 W 3rd Street , ☏ +1574 223-3397 .
#Text=A week in July of livestock shows , community building projects , and county fair food come together to make a time that 's hard to beat .
#Text=Haunted Woods Trail , 37 E 375 N ( At the Fulton County Museum , see below ) .
#Text=The Historical Society grounds are turned into a scary walk in the woods for the two weekends before Halloween . $ 6 for ages 12 and up , $ 3 ages 6-11 , free for 5 and under .
#Text=Historical Power Show , 37 E 375 N ( At the Fulton County Museum , see below ) .
#Text=Owners of historical tractors and other such machinery gather in an open-to-the-public festival every June . $ 5 , free for 11 and under .
#Text=Living History Faire , 37 E 375 N ( At the Fulton County Museum , see below ) .

#Text=An indoor festival held every March , the Living History Faire showcases experts and vendors from all different historical times and places , ranging from 1700s Russia to Civil War-era America to pre-Columbus Indian lore .
#Text=Redbud Trail Rendezvous , 37 E 375 N ( At the Fulton County Museum , see below ) .
#Text=A living history festival in April with historical goods , food , experts , and reenactors from the 1800s . $ 3 ages 12 and up , 11 and under free .
#Text=Round Barn Festival .

#Text=Paying tribute to the county 's claim to fame as the Round Barn Capital of the World , downtown is turned into a big festival on a weekend in June with all kinds of activities and local vendors , as well as a twilight parade .
#Text=Free admission .
#Text=Trail of Courage , 37 E 375 N ( At the Fulton County Museum , see below ) .

#Text=The largest event put on by the Fulton County Historical Society , the Trail of Courage is an 1800s living history festival held in September based off of the Trail of Death , which spent its first night near Rochester .
#Text=Historical experts , vendors , reenactors , food made on location , and activities of all sorts can be found . $ 7 ages 12 and up , $ 3 ages 6-11 , $ 2 each bus students , 5 and under free .
#Text=Suds in the City , 703 Main Street .
#Text=An annual tasting festival featuring all kinds of Indiana craft beers .
#Text=What 's not to like ? $ 20 in advance , $ 25 at the door .
#Text=Indoor Activities
#Text=Farmer 's Market , 37 E 375 N ( At the Fulton County Museum , see below ) .
#Text=Local gardeners and farmers gather to sell their produce and other goodies most Saturdays and Wednesdays .
#Text=Fulton County Public Library Rochester Branch , 320 W 7th Street , ☏ +1574 223-2713 .

#Text=The largest library in the county has a wide collection of media , a room full of historical and genealogical materials , free computer access and wi-fi , and a small rotating local art gallery .
#Text=WROI Radio Station , 110 E 8th Street , ☏ +1574 223-6059 .
#Text=" The Window on 8th Street " , 92.1 WROI 's station is open for visits and tours .
#Text=Outdoor Activities
#Text=Elks Lodge No.
#Text=2120 Golf Course
#Text=S Country Club Drive , ☏ +1574 223-3704 .
#Text=A 9-hole golf course at the local Elks lodge .
#Text=Rochester City Park .
#Text=A large park with numerous pavilions , picnic tables , and areas for various sports all surrounding Manitou Mountain , a massive playground .
#Text=Rochester Community Swimming Pool .
#Text=12PM-8PM Monday - Saturday , 1PM-8PM Sunday , generally closed when the air 's under 70 degrees .
#Text=The city pool ranges from 3 to 12 feet deep with two waterslides .
#Text=There 's also a small wading pool for younger children and a concession stand .
#Text=It 's right by the driving range and putting green for the Round Barn Golf Club at Mill Creek , making it perfect to hit a bucket , then wind down at the pool . $ 3 ages 5 and up .
#Text=Round Barn Golf Club at Mill Creek , 1024 Lakeview Drive , ☏ +1574 223-5717 .
#Text=A 72-par 18-hole golf course on Mill Creek .
#Text=Its clubhouse is the restored Gerig Round Barn , giving it one of the most unique features of any golf course .
#Text=It 's commonly referred to by its old name , Mill Creek Golf Course , or simply Mill Creek .
